Implement real Source Management UI in Angular admin app:
apps/admin-web

ASSUMPTIONS
- JWT auth exists + interceptor attaches token.
- Routes exist including /sources.
- Backend endpoints exist:
  GET/POST/PUT/DELETE /api/v1/sources and POST /api/v1/sources/{id}/toggle-active

GOALS
- /sources page shows sources from API
- Admin can add/edit/delete/toggle active
- Non-admin can only view (read-only)
- Basic filters and pagination.

A) API SERVICE
Create src/app/services/sources-api.service.ts
Methods:
1692967947214471168-xLfu4WP2KCTxKi0bMkyta3V6yPu67v
- list(params) => GET /api/v1/sources
- get(id) => GET /api/v1/sources/{id}
- create(payload) => POST /api/v1/sources
- update(id,payload) => PUT /api/v1/sources/{id}
- delete(id) => DELETE /api/v1/sources/{id}
- toggleActive(id,isActive) => POST /api/v1/sources/{id}/toggle-active

Use baseUrl from src/app/shared/api.config.ts

B) SOURCES PAGE UI (src/app/pages/sources)
Replace placeholder with:
1) Filters row:
- q (text)
- type dropdown (All, RSS, X, Manual, GoogleNews)
- category text (or dropdown if you prefer)
- isActive dropdown (All/Active/Passive)
- Search button

2) Table columns:
Name | Type | Identifier | Url | Category | Trust | Priority | Active | DefaultBehavior | Updated | Actions

3) Actions:
- Admin only:
  - Add Source button -> opens modal form
  - Edit button per row -> opens modal
  - Delete button -> confirm
  - Active toggle switch -> calls toggleActive
- Non-admin:
  - no actions; just table

4) Modal form (no external UI libs):
Fields:
- name
- type (RSS/X/Manual/GoogleNews)
- identifier (only when type=X)
- url (only when type=RSS)
- category
- trustLevel (0..100)
- priority (0..1000)
- defaultBehavior (Auto/Editorial)
- isActive (checkbox)

Validation:
- show inline errors; disable Save when invalid
- if type=RSS require valid url
- if type=X require identifier (strip @ if user pasted)

C) ROLE CHECKS
Use AuthService roles:
- isAdmin = roles includes "Admin"

D) ROUTING/MENU
Ensure sidebar shows "Sources" to all logged-in users, but page is read-only for non-admin.

E) UX
- On save/delete/toggle show a simple alert (or inline message)
- Refresh list after changes
- Disable buttons while saving

OUTPUT
- Files changed
- Manual test steps